The paper deals with Private Information Retrieval (PIR) in distributed storage systems, which involves coding techniques and protocols for retrieving information from a database stored across multiple servers. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), distributed systems (cs.DS), cryptography (cs.CR), coding theory (cs.CC), and security and privacy (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
